content.content:
[{"type": "section", "value": {"heading": "Just for sanity's sake", "level": 1, "content": [{"type": "rich_text", "value": "

Just is, basically, a command-runner, and it's been a blessing in my life. What have I done to \"just run commands\" in the past? The standard journey goes:

  • Excessive use of `man` pages
  • Abusive `grep`ping of `history`
  • A constant addition of aliases and functions to your shell at `.profile` time
  • Pipenv `[scripts]`, npm \"scripts\", etc.
  • Make?
  • CMake?!
  • Maybe just a bunch of .sh files under `scripts/`?

All those things have scarred me, and a Justfile has been my salvation. In short, my Justfile feels like the perfect compromise between Make and the bunch of shell scripts.

content.title: Just for sanity's sake
content.content:
[{"type": "section", "value": {"heading": "Just for sanity's sake", "level": 1, "content": [{"type": "rich_text", "value": "

Just is basically a command-runner, and a great blessing in my life. What have I done to \"just run commands\" in the past? The standard journey goes:

  • Excessive use of man pages
  • Abusive grepping of history
  • A constant addition of aliases and functions to your shell at .profile time
  • Pipenv [scripts], npm \"scripts\", etc.
  • Make?
  • CMake?!
  • Maybe just a bunch of .sh files under scripts/?

All those things have scarred me, and a Justfile was my salvation. In short, my Justfile feels like the perfect compromise between Make and the bunch of shell scripts.

", "id": "e94c1825-0ce5-4ff5-bbaf-80779e6e78af"}]}, "id": "9fc3b564-73cb-4737-b08a-5c574a75e1a7"}]
